NAME
    App::perlmv::scriptlet::prefix_with_number - Prefix filenames with
    number (usually to make them easily sortable)

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.002 of
    App::perlmv::scriptlet::prefix_with_number (from Perl distribution
    App-perlmv-scriptlet-prefix_with_number), released on 2026-03-27.

SYNOPSIS
    The default is sorted ascibetically:

     % perlmv prefix-with-number foo bar.txt baz.mp3

     1-bar.txt
     2-baz.mp3
     3-foo

    Don't sort ("-T" perlmv option), use two digits:

     % perlmv prefix-with-number -T -a digits=2 foo bar.txt baz.mp3

     01-foo
     02-bar.txt
     03-baz.mp3

DESCRIPTION
SCRIPTLET ARGUMENTS
    Arguments can be passed using the "-a" ("--arg") perlmv option, e.g. "-a
    name=val".

  digits
    Required. Number of digits to use (1 means 1,2,3,..., 2 means
    01,02,03,...); the default is to autodetect.

  inc
    Increment from one number to the next.

  start
    Number to start from.

